benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/catalog/simplePlan - Add a simple plan entry in the current version of the catalog

covered: Valid Payload: TC01 and TC02 demonstrate successful creation with valid payloads.

Invalid Payload and Validation: TC03 (missing header), TC04 (missing planId), TC05 (invalid currency), TC08 (empty body), TC09 (malformed JSON), TC12 (maximum field lengths), TC13 (minimum field values), TC18 (input with potential XSS/SQL injection).
Duplicate Submission: TC06 tests conflict on existing planId.
Large Payloads: TC15 tests very large payloads.
Server/Dependency Resilience: TC11 (503 service unavailable) and TC16/TC23/TC24 cover various dependency issues and recovery scenarios.
Method Handling: TC14 tests 405 for unsupported HTTP method.
gaps: Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling or burst handling of concurrent POST requests.
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) in POST responses.
500 Internal Server Error: No explicit 500 error scenario; only 503 covered.
Additional boundary tests could be considered for edge-case payload sizes.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting/throttling tests and idempotency checks for duplicate submissions.
Introduce tests for 500 Internal Server Error scenarios to verify retry and error handling behavior.
Add tests for caching headers on POST responses if applicable (ETag/Cache-Control).
Extend test coverage for boundary conditions around payload size and field lengths.
